cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.AI, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) - The problem of terrain guarding involves finding a set of guard locations on a terrain, which is a classic problem in computational geometry. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The proposed algorithm is a 2-approximation algorithm that runs in O($n \log m$) time, which suggests that it involves the use of efficient data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The problem of terrain guarding involves discrete objects (points, lines, and polygons) and their relationships, which is a topic of interest in discrete mathematics. 
4. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The problem of terrain guarding can be seen as a task of finding an optimal solution to a combinatorial optimization problem, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The problem of terrain guarding is known to be NP-complete, which is a topic of interest in computational complexity theory.
